    "descriptionModule": {
      "briefSummary": "The ANTHEM-HFpEF Study is designed to demonstrate the safety and efficacy of vagus nerve stimulation (VNS) with the Cyberonics VNS Therapy System for the treatment of subjects with symptomatic heart failure with preserved and mid-range ejection fraction.",
      "detailedDescription": "Heart failure patients will be enrolled and implanted with a cervical VNS system on the right side. After a 2-week post-implantation recovery period and a 10-week stimulation titration period, continuous periodic stimulation will be performed for 12 months, with data collection at 3, 6, 9, and 12 months."
    },
